OL,3,CAdvice as region see increase in
OL,4,Cwhopping cough and respiratory
OL,5,Cillnesses
OL,7,F"If you have symptoms, please avoid
OL,8,Fcontact with other people.
OL,10,F"When you no longer have a fever and
OL,11,Fdon't need medicine to control your
OL,12,Ffever, you can return to normal
OL,13,Factivities."
OL,15,FFor some people, respiratory illness
OL,16,Fcan be more serious and require
OL,17,Ftreatment. The NHS says you should
OL,18,Fseek medical advice from a pharmacist
OL,19,For GP if you are concerned.
